    15	## Runtime surface
    16	
    17	The canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:
    18	
    19	- `Engine.open(...)`
    20	- `engine.write(...)`
    21	- `engine.search(...)`
    22	- `engine.close()`
    23	- `admin.configure(...)`
    24	
    25	All runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.
    26	
    27	`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report
    28	owned by `design/engine.md`.
    29	
    30	> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The napi-rs binding currently
    31	> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.
    32	> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:
    33	OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing
    34	> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need
    35	> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage
    36	> data wait for 0.6.1.
    37	
    38	`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`
    39	member carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:
    40	
    41	- `embedderPoolSize`
    42	- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`
    43	- `provenanceRowCap`
    44	- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`
    45	- `slowThresholdMs`
    46	
    47	If TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a
    48	TS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config
    49	field and not a Python parity obligation.
    50	
    51	## Engine-attached instrumentation / control
    52	
    53	These are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:
    54	
    55	- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`
    56	- `engine.counters()`
    57	- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`
    58	- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`
    59	
    60	Subscriber attachment is provided by:
    61	
    62	- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`
    63	
    64	`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in
    65	`design/bindings.md`.
    66	
    67	## Caller-visible data shapes
    68	
    69	- `WriteReceipt.cursor`
    70	- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`

