## Verdict: CONCERN

### 1. [medium] Parity matrix overstates completion while TS is still missing
Refs: [dev/notes/12-TX-parity-matrix.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/notes/12-TX-parity-matrix.md:21), [dev/notes/12-TX-parity-matrix.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/notes/12-TX-parity-matrix.md:32), [dev/plans/prompts/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-ts.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-ts.md:11)

The matrix legend says `✅` means both surfaces are present, but the row itself says TS is still pending and only flips to fully `✅` after the TS slice lands. That makes the table internally contradictory and overstates current parity for this row.

### 2. [medium] REQ-064 coverage is updated in `acceptance.md`, but `dev/traceability.md` is still stale
Refs: [dev/acceptance.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/acceptance.md:1170), [dev/traceability.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/traceability.md:55), [dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-output.json](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-output.json:46)

The REQ→AC coverage row in `acceptance.md` now lists `AC-068a/b/c/d`, but `dev/traceability.md` still stops at `AC-068a/b` for the security-hardening trace. Since the closure artifact claims the coverage trace is updated, one trace source remains stale and should be brought back into sync.

## What passed on inspection

- Shape D is implemented correctly. `Engine.open` still returns just `Engine`, the report is stashed on `PyEngine` at open time, and `engine.open_report()` is an engine-attached accessor rather than a return-shape change. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:387), [src/python/fathomdb/engine.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/fathomdb/engine.py:54), [src/python/fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi:47)
- Field fidelity is good. The Python surface preserves the native identifiers verbatim: `schema_version_before`, `schema_version_after`, `migration_steps`, `embedder_warmup_ms`, `query_backend`, `default_embedder`. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:541), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:357), [src/python/fathomdb/types.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/fathomdb/types.py:68)
- Idempotency looks sound in code and test. The binding captures the report once during open and returns a clone on each accessor call, so there is no re-probe or live-state read. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:397), [src/python/tests/test_openreport.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/tests/test_openreport.py:44)
- The PyO3 choice is reasonable. `#[pyclass(frozen, get_all)]` is used for `OpenReport`, `MigrationStepReport`, and `EmbedderIdentity`, and the nested types are attribute-accessible from Python. The stored report is plain Rust-owned data, so I did not see a GIL/thread-safety foot-gun in this pattern. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:329)
- TDD evidence is credible. Before this commit, the Python wrapper and stub had no `open_report`, so the reported `AttributeError` RED is plausible; the new test exercises all six top-level fields, idempotency, and unchanged `Engine.open` return shape. Refs: [src/python/tests/test_openreport.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/tests/test_openreport.py:22), [src/python/fathomdb/engine.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/fathomdb/engine.py:117), baseline [src/python/fathomdb/engine.py](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/src/python/fathomdb/engine.py:54)
- The Python interface/spec edits are clean. The caveat block is removed, the open-line is rewritten to point at the accessor, and `engine.open_report()` is added to the engine-attached list. Refs: [dev/interfaces/python.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/interfaces/python.md:25)
- AC-068d’s placeholder wording is self-consistent with the pending TS slice: the accessor is described as sync in both the acceptance entry and the TS slice prompt. Refs: [dev/acceptance.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/acceptance.md:1059), [dev/plans/prompts/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-ts.md](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-OPENREPORT-py-20260524T195358Z/dev/plans/prompts/0.6.1-OPENREPORT-ts.md:11)

